        public <P extends PrimitiveRecord> boolean removePropertyIfExists​(RecordAccess.RecordProxy<P,​Void> primitiveProxy,
                                                                  int propertyKey,
                                                                  RecordAccess<PropertyRecord,​PrimitiveRecord> propertyRecords)
        Removes property with given propertyKey from property chain owner by the primitive found in primitiveProxy if it exists.
        Parameters:
        primitiveProxy - access to the primitive record pointing to the start of the property chain.
        propertyKey - the property key token id to look for and remove.
        propertyRecords - access to records.
        Returns:
        true if the property was found and removed, otherwise false.

        Removes property with given propertyKey from property chain owner by the primitive found in primitiveProxy.
        Parameters:
        primitiveProxy - access to the primitive record pointing to the start of the property chain.
        propertyKey - the property key token id to look for and remove.
        propertyRecords - access to records.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if property key was not found in the property chain.
